

Security Deposit: Max 1 month’s rent.

Early Termination: Allowed with 30 days’ notice; penalty ≤ 1 month’s rent.

Maintenance: Landlord handles major repairs (HVAC, plumbing, structure, appliances).

Renewal: Converts to month-to-month after initial term; no auto-renewal.

Pets: Allow small pets (under 25–30 lbs) with reasonable deposit.

Rent Increase: Max 5% per year; 60 days’ notice required.

Subletting: Allowed with landlord’s written approval.

Utilities: Clearly defined—prefer included or separated by unit.

Entry Notice: 24–48 hours required (except emergencies).

Parking: At least one space included; extra at reasonable rate.

Late Fees: Max 5% of rent, 5-day grace period.

Damage & Wear: Normal wear and tear not charged.

Habitability: Right to withhold rent if serious issues unaddressed (with notice).

Lease Transfer: Permitted with landlord approval.

Security Deposit Return: Within 14–21 days with itemized deductions.

Move-in Inspection: Required with written checklist.
